{
  "text": "Bayesian decoding inverts the encoding model to find the posterior distribution P( jr), which describes how likely each direction is given the observed responses (Földiák, 1994; Salinas & Abbott, 1994; [CITATION_1] . For example, under an independent Poisson noise assumption,",
